## Agent Step Logging

Every tool call and its result gets logged to the agent_steps table.
This is how Pem shows "what I did" on the prep detail screen.
It's also useful for debugging.

Log on every `onStepFinish` callback from Vercel AI SDK.

---

## Database Tables

### users

Synced from Clerk webhook on user.created.

| Column     | Type      | Notes                          |
| ---------- | --------- | ------------------------------ |
| id         | uuid      | primary key                    |
| clerk_id   | text      | unique, from Clerk             |
| email      | text      |                                |
| name       | text      | nullable                       |
| push_token | text      | Expo push token, nullable      |
| created_at | timestamp |                                |

### dumps

One row per text submission from the user.

| Column     | Type      | Notes                    |
| ---------- | --------- | ------------------------ |
| id         | uuid      | primary key              |
| user_id    | uuid      | FK → users               |
| raw_text   | text      | exactly what user typed  |
| created_at | timestamp |                          |

### preps

One row per thought extracted from a dump.

| Column       | Type      | Notes                                                |
| ------------ | --------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| id           | uuid      | primary key                                          |
| user_id      | uuid      | FK → users                                           |
| dump_id      | uuid      | FK → dumps                                           |
| thought      | text      | the specific thought being prepped                     |
| context      | jsonb     | enriched context at time of creation                 |
| status       | text      | prepping / ready / archived / failed                 |
| summary      | text      | short preview shown on card                            |
| result       | jsonb     | full structured result                               |
| render_type  | text      | search / research / options / draft / compound       |
| created_at   | timestamp |                                                      |
| ready_at     | timestamp | nullable                                             |
| archived_at  | timestamp | nullable                                             |

### user_profile

Key-value store. One row per fact per user.
This is how Pem remembers things about the user over time.

| Column     | Type      | Notes                                      |
| ---------- | --------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| id         | uuid      | primary key                                |
| user_id    | uuid      | FK → users                                 |
| key        | text      | fact name e.g. "car", "location", "name"   |
| value      | text      | fact value e.g. "2019 Honda Civic"           |
| source     | text      | which dump_id or prep_id this came from      |
| created_at | timestamp |                                            |
| updated_at | timestamp | updated on upsert                          |

Upsert on (user_id, key). Latest value wins.

### agent_steps

One row per tool call the agent made during a prep.
Used for the "what Pem did" log on the detail screen.

| Column      | Type      | Notes                                              |
| ----------- | --------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| id          | uuid      | primary key                                        |
| prep_id     | uuid      | FK → preps                                         |
| step_number | int       | order of this step                                 |
| tool_name   | text      | search / fetch / remember / save / draft / clarify |
| tool_input  | jsonb     | what the agent passed to the tool                    |
| tool_output | jsonb     | what the tool returned                             |
| thinking    | text      | agent's reasoning before this step (if available)    |
| created_at  | timestamp |                                                    |

