## Profile — How Memory Works

The user_profile table is a simple key-value store.
The agent reads from it via remember() and writes to it via save().
It grows silently with every prep — the user never fills a form.

**What gets saved:**

```
name, location, job, car, family members and their interests,
typical budget ranges, recurring contacts, preferred services,
anything specific mentioned that would help future preps
```

**How remember() works:**
Reads from user_profile where user_id = current user AND key = requested key.
Returns the value or null.

**How save() works:**
Upserts into user_profile (user_id, key) → sets value, source, updated_at.

**Profile is shown to user in settings:**
Users can see and delete any fact Pem has saved about them.
This is the trust/privacy layer.

---

## Build Order

Build in this sequence. Each step must work before the next.

```
1. DB schema — all five tables via Drizzle
2. Clerk webhook → user created in DB
3. Auth guard — JWT verification
4. POST /dumps → split → return immediately (no agent yet, just log thoughts)
5. BullMQ worker setup — job queued and picked up
6. remember() and save() tools — profile read/write working
7. search() tool — Tavily connected
8. Agent loop — generateText with search + remember + save
9. Step logging — every tool call saved to agent_steps
10. draft() tool — generates email/message
11. fetch() tool — URL fetching
12. clarify() tool — pause/resume flow
13. render_type classifier — set after agent finishes
14. Push notification on ready
15. GET /preps — cards returned to frontend
16. GET /preps/:id — full result + steps
17. PATCH /preps/:id/archive
18. POST /preps/:id/clarify — user reply resumes job
```

---

## LLM Routing

```
Split agent              → gpt-4o-mini   (fast, cheap, simple extraction)
Prep agent               → gpt-4o        (the main agent — reasoning, tool use)
Draft tool               → gpt-4o        (better writing voice)
Render type classifier   → gpt-4o-mini   (simple classification after agent done)
Summary generator        → gpt-4o-mini   (one sentence for card preview)
```

---

## Rules

- Text only for now. No voice. No audio. No Whisper.
- Return from POST /dumps immediately — never await agents.
- One thought = one BullMQ job = one prep row = one card.
- Agent decides its own steps — never hardcode routing logic.
- Call remember() before searching when the profile might already have the fact.
- Call save() when the user states a durable fact about themselves (vehicle, job, etc.) and when you learn something new from tools.
- Log every agent step to agent_steps via onStepFinish.
- Max 3 options if result includes options.
- Max 1 clarify call per prep.
- Prep status only moves forward: prepping → ready → archived.
- Failed preps stay as failed — never shown as ready.
- Pem never sends, buys, or acts. It only prepares.
- render_type is set after agent finishes — not before.
- Profile is user-visible and user-deletable in settings.

